Bring a large #saucepan{} of water with @salt{1/2%tsp} to the boil. Chop the
@potatoes{450%grams} into 2cm chunks (peel first if you prefer).

When boiling, add the potatoes to the water and cook until you can easily slip
a #knife{} through, ~{15-20%minutes}.

Meanwhile, trim the @carrot{1}, then quarter lengthways (no need to peel).
Chop widthways into 1cm pieces.

Peel and grate the @garlic cloves{2}(peeled and grated) (or use a #garlic press{}).

Heat a drizzle of @oil{drizzle} in a large #frying pan{} on high heat.

Once hot, add the @British beef mince{240%grams} and carrot. Fry until the mince
has browned, ~{5-6%minutes}. Use a #spoon{} to break it up as it cooks.

When the mince has browned, drain and discard any excess fat. Season with
@salt{pinch} and @ground black pepper{pinch}.

> IMPORTANT: Wash your hands and equipment after handling raw mince. It's cooked
> when no longer pink in the middle.

Stir the garlic into the beef and fry for ~{1%minute} more.

Add the @finely chopped tomatoes{1/2%carton}, @dried rosemary{1%sachet},
@red wine stock paste{28%grams}, @Worcester sauce{15%grams},
@tomato ketchup{1%tbsp}, @sugar{1/2%tsp} and @water{50%milliliters} for the
sauce.

Stir together, bring to the boil, then reduce the heat and simmer, stirring
occasionally, until thickened, ~{4-5%minutes}. Taste and season with salt and
pepper if needed.

Meanwhile, grate the @Red Leicester{30%grams}.

> TIP: Keep the remaining chopped tomatoes for another recipe.

Once the potatoes are cooked, drain in a #colander{} and return to the pan,
off the heat. Add a @butter{knob} and a splash of @milk{if you have any} and
mash with a #potato masher{} until smooth.

Season with salt and pepper. Cover with a #lid{} to keep warm.

Preheat your #grill{} to its highest setting.

Pour the beef mixture into an appropriately sized #ovenproof dish{}, then top
with the mash, using a spoon to smooth the top of the surface.

Use the Red Leicester cheese to create a spooky pumpkin or ghost shape on the
top of your pie.

Grill your pie until the cheese has melted, ~{4-5%minutes}.

> TIP: Pop the dish onto a #baking tray{} to catch any drips.

Meanwhile, wipe out the mince pan and pop on medium-high heat with a drizzle of
@oil{drizzle}.

Once hot, add the @peas{120%grams} and stir-fry for ~{2-3%minutes}.

Share the creepy cottage pie between your #plates{} with the peas alongside.

Enjoy!